      "feedback": "The plan correctly unmasks, starts (when appropriate), and enables auditd, which will resolve the vulnerability. Adding package presence checks and verifying the service started successfully would make it more robust.",
      "concerns": [
        "The plan does not verify that the audit package is installed before attempting to enable the service.",
        "No verification is performed after starting the service to ensure it is running.",
        "It does not reload the systemd daemon after unmasking, which could be required on some systems."
      ],
      "suggested_improvements": [
        "Add a check like `rpm -q audit` (or appropriate package manager command) to confirm the audit package is present before proceeding.",
        "After `systemctl start auditd.service`, run `systemctl is-active auditd.service` and handle failures.",
